<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hang someone out to dry • leave someone hanging</xh5><p> <i>hang someone out to dry</i>—(coll.) not support or help smb.; abandon a person when he is in trouble: I made a mistake that made a customer very angry and my boss really <u>hung me out to dry</u>!</p><p> <i>leave someone hanging</i>—(coll.) keep smb. waiting for a decision or answer: When Amal had to leave for work, he left his exciting story unfinished. We were frustrated that he <u>left us hanging</u>.</p> </entry>
